<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1301] HTable.getRow() returns null if the row does no exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1301</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HBase API docs says when the row does not exist, getRow() returns&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    RowResult is empty if row does not exist. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, in regionserver/HRegionServer.java&apos;s getRow():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      if (result == null || result.isEmpty())&lt;br/&gt;
        return null;&lt;br/&gt;
      return new RowResult(row, result);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It actually returns null. Either fix the code or the document.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
