       checkOOME(e);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The commit mentions &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-847&quot; title=&quot;new API: HTable.getRow with numVersion specified&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-847&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-847&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; new API: HTable.getRow with numVersion specified&quot; but that doesn&apos;t seem to be the right issue.  This seems to be it &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1028&quot; title=&quot;If key does not exist, return null in getRow rather than an empty RowResult&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1028&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1028&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, yeah, seems like its the doc thats wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
